1
00:01:40,298 --> 00:01:42,508
It's okay! Just let go!

2
00:01:51,976 --> 00:01:55,021
You can't save me, kid!
You can't pull me up!

3
00:01:55,021 --> 00:01:57,023
Please! I don't
want you to fall!

4
00:01:59,275 --> 00:02:00,568
What are you doing?

5
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,452
What the hell is wrong
with the two of you?

6
00:02:09,452 --> 00:02:11,496
You trying to get
yourselves killed?

7
00:02:18,085 --> 00:02:20,046
What the hell? My arm...

8
00:02:20,046 --> 00:02:21,756
I just moved it, didn't I?

9
00:02:21,756 --> 00:02:23,424
Yeah!

10
00:02:23,424 --> 00:02:24,717
Your welcome.

11
00:02:25,384 --> 00:02:27,720
So, you mean that
wasn't just a fluke?

12
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:30,139
You really think you
can heal it for me?

13
00:02:30,139 --> 00:02:32,600
Sure, we can have you back
to normal in no time.

14
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,893
Shouldn't be too much trouble.

15
00:02:33,893 --> 00:02:36,103
It's actually a rather
simple procedure.

16
00:02:36,103 --> 00:02:38,439
Is there anything that's
not simple to him?

17
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:41,067
You mean
"back to normal" as in...

18
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:42,819
You think I could box again?

19
00:02:42,819 --> 00:02:50,034
Boxing? Don't be ridiculous.

20
00:02:50,034 --> 00:02:52,370
When I'm done with you,
you'll be able to compete

21
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:54,372
in the world
arm-wrestling championship!

22
00:02:58,709 --> 00:03:01,087
That joke was stupid
and completely tasteless!

23
00:03:01,087 --> 00:03:02,421
Well taste this!

24
00:03:06,175 --> 00:03:07,343
Hey I'm home.

25
00:03:11,889 --> 00:03:13,850
Something seems to be
bothering the boy.

26
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:18,980
As his father it is my duty
to get to the bottom of this.

27
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:20,898
Honey can you give
me a hand with this,

28
00:03:20,898 --> 00:03:23,442
the lid is stuck and I
can't seem to get it open.

29
00:03:23,442 --> 00:03:24,652
Well of course my darling.

30
00:03:24,652 --> 00:03:27,530
No need for you to trouble
yourself, leave it to me.

31
00:03:27,530 --> 00:03:28,948
It's stuck!

32
00:03:28,948 --> 00:03:32,159
Come on you stupid
jar of tomato sauce!

33
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,911
Sweetheart, it isn't
that big a deal.

34
00:03:33,911 --> 00:03:35,162
I said it's no problem!

35
00:03:35,162 --> 00:03:36,873
Maybe I should run
hot water over it.

36
00:03:36,873 --> 00:03:37,957
Would you stop interrupting me?!

37
00:03:37,957 --> 00:03:40,334
You're breaking
my concentration!

38
00:03:40,334 --> 00:03:43,129
Wow. You know, you're
doing a damn good job

39
00:03:43,129 --> 00:03:44,380
for a jar of
tomato sauce.

40
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:45,506
Right back at ya!

41
00:03:45,506 --> 00:03:49,093
I'll just go grab another jar.

42
00:03:49,093 --> 00:03:49,719
Here.

43
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,803
What?

44
00:03:54,015 --> 00:03:54,891
Are you okay?

45
00:03:54,891 --> 00:03:56,601
Yes. I'm fine.

46
00:03:58,853 --> 00:04:00,730
Kenichi was always a weak kid,

47
00:04:00,730 --> 00:04:02,732
when did he become stronger
than his own father?

48
00:04:02,732 --> 00:04:06,110
I feel sad, happy, proud and
ashamed all at the same time!

49
00:04:06,110 --> 00:04:08,487
I'm so conflicted, tomato sauce.

50
00:04:08,487 --> 00:04:10,281
I know what ya' mean.

51
00:04:11,908 --> 00:04:15,286
Okay I kinda get this. If a guy
wants to get a girl's attention,

52
00:04:15,286 --> 00:04:17,413
then he needs to
be very assertive.

53
00:04:17,413 --> 00:04:21,500
The stupid book doesn't say how
you tell her that you like her.

54
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:25,588
Besides Miu isn't the easiest
person in the world to approach.

55
00:04:28,007 --> 00:04:30,176
I'd say something to
her at Ryozanpaku,

56
00:04:30,176 --> 00:04:31,510
but we're both too busy working,

57
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:33,262
there isn't a lotta
time for chit-chat.

58
00:04:33,262 --> 00:04:35,723
if things stay the way they are,
then it's completely pointless

59
00:04:35,723 --> 00:04:37,475
for me to keep going
there for training.

60
00:04:37,475 --> 00:04:39,143
Here it comes!

61
00:04:39,143 --> 00:04:42,230
That one time we went out it
didn't really go like I planned.

62
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:46,901
If I just had one more chance,
I know I could win her over!

63
00:04:46,901 --> 00:04:48,069
Kenichi...

64
00:04:48,069 --> 00:04:49,737
Whatcha reading,
can I have a look?

65
00:04:49,737 --> 00:04:52,698
I'm not reading anything! How in
the world did you get in here?

66
00:04:52,698 --> 00:04:54,575
Didn't anyone ever teach
you that you should knock,

67
00:04:54,575 --> 00:04:55,451
you little twerp!

68
00:04:55,451 --> 00:04:57,328
What is it?! Come
on let me see it!

69
00:04:57,328 --> 00:04:58,496
Secrets are no fun!

70
00:04:58,496 --> 00:05:01,916
Get out of here you little
brat or I'll tell Mom!

71
00:05:01,916 --> 00:05:03,709
Interesting, who
would've thought

72
00:05:03,709 --> 00:05:07,880
that the goodbye is what makes
a successful first date.

73
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,383
Where did you come from?!

74
00:05:10,383 --> 00:05:12,468
You're never going to get
anywhere if you keep

75
00:05:12,468 --> 00:05:14,679
getting your advice from
these silly books!

76
00:05:14,679 --> 00:05:17,014
Kenichi, you can't
learn to woo a woman

77
00:05:17,014 --> 00:05:18,432
by reading a how-to book.

78
00:05:18,432 --> 00:05:21,936
It's not a science
it's an art form!

79
00:05:21,936 --> 00:05:24,188
Dad, you are so the
coolest guy ever!

80
00:05:24,188 --> 00:05:25,439
No you don't understand,

81
00:05:25,439 --> 00:05:27,275
without that book I won't
have any confidence!

82
00:05:27,275 --> 00:05:29,026
C'mon you're
being ridiculous!

83
00:05:29,026 --> 00:05:31,320
When I was a young man,
we were driven by passion

84
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,697
and not some stupid book!

85
00:05:32,697 --> 00:05:35,449
I didn't even pursue your
mother, she came after me.

86
00:05:35,449 --> 00:05:38,244
She bugged me until I
finally asked her out.

87
00:05:38,244 --> 00:05:41,414
She used to write me romantic
letters every single day.

88
00:05:41,414 --> 00:05:43,541
You wouldn't believe some
of the things she would say

89
00:05:43,541 --> 00:05:45,960
in those notes--
they'd knock your socks off!

90
00:05:47,545 --> 00:05:48,587
That's nice and all,

91
00:05:48,587 --> 00:05:50,715
but I don't think
Miu's that type of girl.

92
00:05:50,715 --> 00:05:53,426
You're still hung
up on Blondie?!

93
00:05:53,426 --> 00:05:56,345
This was a good talk, son. Just
remember, if you're always

94
00:05:56,345 --> 00:05:59,807
sincere and honest with your
lady you're on the right track!

95
00:06:02,685 --> 00:06:04,895
So I should be
sincere and honest.

96
00:06:04,895 --> 00:06:07,440
Yeah but Miu and I aren't even
boyfriend and girlfriend yet.

97
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,275
It's hopeless.

98
00:06:09,275 --> 00:06:11,652
Well isn't that odd.
The way I remember it,

99
00:06:11,652 --> 00:06:13,321
you were the one
writing the love letters

100
00:06:13,321 --> 00:06:14,989
and begging me
to go out with you!

101
00:06:14,989 --> 00:06:17,742
If you'd like, I can read them
aloud for the children so they

102
00:06:17,742 --> 00:06:20,995
can see what kind of "manly"
guy their father really is!

103
00:06:20,995 --> 00:06:23,581
Honey, cut me some
slack! I'm so sorry!

104
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:28,085
So the kid took Takeda out, huh?

105
00:06:28,085 --> 00:06:29,337
That's right.

106
00:06:29,337 --> 00:06:31,255
Did I call it or what?

107
00:06:31,255 --> 00:06:33,090
That's what happens
when you send a boxer

108
00:06:33,090 --> 00:06:35,134
to do a real fighters job!

109
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:38,846
Shut your mouth Tsuji.

110
00:06:38,846 --> 00:06:41,974
If I wanted your opinion
I'd ask for it.

111
00:06:41,974 --> 00:06:44,560
I'm impressed. The boy's
done well for himself.

112
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:47,354
He's lasted a lot longer
than I thought!

113
00:06:48,481 --> 00:06:50,608
You're trying to expand
the gang, but that kid's

114
00:06:50,608 --> 00:06:52,818
beating your people faster
than you can recruit them!

115
00:06:52,818 --> 00:06:54,236
Executive member or not,

116
00:06:54,236 --> 00:06:58,908
Tsuji has no right to speak to
Kisara with such disrespect!

117
00:06:58,908 --> 00:07:01,452
This Kenichi kid, we've
got to do something,

118
00:07:01,452 --> 00:07:03,162
we can't leave him
out on his own,

119
00:07:03,162 --> 00:07:05,498
if he decides to join with some
other group besides Ragnarok,

120
00:07:05,498 --> 00:07:07,124
that'll be a big problem for us!

121
00:07:07,124 --> 00:07:09,043
Well, that's putting it mildly.

122
00:07:13,506 --> 00:07:15,132
We need a new approach.

123
00:07:15,132 --> 00:07:18,344
If he won't join us, then
I'll just have to kill him.

124
00:07:18,344 --> 00:07:19,553
Wait just a second!

125
00:07:19,553 --> 00:07:20,429
No.

126
00:07:20,429 --> 00:07:22,598
I said wait!

127
00:07:22,598 --> 00:07:24,642
Do you have a problem
with my plan?

128
00:07:24,642 --> 00:07:28,020
No problem, just gimme a shot.

129
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,939
Let me handle this.

130
00:07:29,939 --> 00:07:31,482
As I'm sure you are all aware,

131
00:07:31,482 --> 00:07:33,234
the fence on the roof
has been damaged.

132
00:07:33,234 --> 00:07:35,152
Now, it may be that
after 60 years,

133
00:07:35,152 --> 00:07:37,988
our campus is simply
falling apart, however,

134
00:07:37,988 --> 00:07:42,618
just to be safe, from now on,
the rooftop is off-limits.

135
00:07:42,618 --> 00:07:47,665
I hope you all try to be
more careful in the future.

136
00:07:47,665 --> 00:07:48,249
Hey.

137
00:07:48,249 --> 00:07:50,126
Weak-knee, I-I mean, Kenichi.

138
00:07:50,126 --> 00:07:52,503
What's happening, can I
help you out with something?

139
00:07:52,503 --> 00:07:56,090
Guys, we really need to talk.
It's about the other day.

140
00:07:58,425 --> 00:08:00,719
I'm pretty sure it was
all my fault that you two

141
00:08:00,719 --> 00:08:03,305
got dragged into what should
have been my fight.

142
00:08:03,305 --> 00:08:05,474
So, I just wanted
to tell you both

143
00:08:05,474 --> 00:08:06,934
that I'm sorry
for what happened.

144
00:08:06,934 --> 00:08:08,936
Uh-huh...

145
00:08:08,936 --> 00:08:10,187
What in the world is he up to?

146
00:08:10,187 --> 00:08:12,606
I don't trust him. I bet
this is some kinda trap.

147
00:08:12,606 --> 00:08:14,150
Normally in this
type of situation,

148
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:16,277
we would be the ones saying
we're sorry wouldn't we?

149
00:08:16,277 --> 00:08:18,237
Because we ran away?

150
00:08:18,237 --> 00:08:20,447
Is it possible that...

151
00:08:20,447 --> 00:08:23,576
...he's really that stupid?

152
00:08:23,576 --> 00:08:26,328
Or is he just a
genuinely good guy?!

153
00:08:26,328 --> 00:08:29,623
Hey it's no big deal,
we're classmates aren't we?

154
00:08:29,623 --> 00:08:30,916
That is such a relief!

155
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,710
So you guys really
do forgive me, right?

156
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:34,128
Uh, sure.

157
00:08:34,128 --> 00:08:36,881
I can't tell you how much
that means to me, I was sure

158
00:08:36,881 --> 00:08:39,216
you guys were gonna hold a
grudge against me forever!

159
00:08:39,216 --> 00:08:40,426
Kenichi!

160
00:08:40,426 --> 00:08:42,803
Okay, just give me a second,
and I'll be right there.

161
00:08:42,803 --> 00:08:44,221
See you guys later!

162
00:08:53,619 --> 00:08:54,244
Miu, listen,

163
00:08:54,244 --> 00:08:56,330
there's something I really
need to talk to you about!

164
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:57,831
Talk is cheap!

165
00:09:01,376 --> 00:09:03,962
Alright, the fight's
over, you're done.

166
00:09:08,008 --> 00:09:10,218
Are you okay? Did I
kick you too hard?

167
00:09:10,218 --> 00:09:11,511
No, it's no problem!

168
00:09:11,511 --> 00:09:12,721
I'm okay.

169
00:09:12,721 --> 00:09:15,057
If she's so worried, maybe
she should take it easy.

170
00:09:15,057 --> 00:09:17,142
Now what was that you
were saying a second ago?

171
00:09:17,142 --> 00:09:19,269
There's something you
wanted to talk to me about?

172
00:09:19,269 --> 00:09:20,854
N-No! It was nothing!

173
00:09:20,854 --> 00:09:23,190
Oh, okay then.

174
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:25,484
Well, I better run to the
kitchen and get dinner started.

175
00:09:25,484 --> 00:09:27,486
See you later.

176
00:09:27,486 --> 00:09:30,113
I couldn't do it,
I chickened out.

177
00:09:30,113 --> 00:09:32,574
I really don't have any courage.

178
00:09:32,574 --> 00:09:34,701
So you need my advice?

179
00:09:34,701 --> 00:09:36,370
You can ask me about
whatever you want,

180
00:09:36,370 --> 00:09:38,330
as long as it doesn't
involve money or women!

181
00:09:38,330 --> 00:09:40,123
Yeah, I shoulda known.

182
00:09:40,123 --> 00:09:42,084
Worthless.

183
00:09:42,084 --> 00:09:47,005
Wow, that kinda hurt my
feelings a little bit...

184
00:09:47,005 --> 00:09:50,509
What's that? You're having
relationship problems?

185
00:09:50,509 --> 00:09:52,094
I must warn you,
this could become

186
00:09:52,094 --> 00:09:54,221
a rather philosophical
discussion, is that alright?

187
00:09:54,221 --> 00:09:55,347
Huh?

188
00:09:59,434 --> 00:10:02,312
As you can see from this formula
love is very complicated.

189
00:10:02,312 --> 00:10:05,107
Uh, thanks, this has
been very educational.

190
00:10:06,942 --> 00:10:08,819
What the heck does
Copernicus have to do

191
00:10:08,819 --> 00:10:10,904
with asking a girl out?

192
00:10:13,115 --> 00:10:15,325
♪ Apapapapapa! ♪

193
00:10:15,325 --> 00:10:17,786
I think we have a
new record. Wow. Go.

194
00:10:17,786 --> 00:10:20,080
I just wish that there was
someone I could talk to

195
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,790
about this type of situation.

196
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:25,961
Someone with a
little experience.

197
00:10:25,961 --> 00:10:28,672
Someone who really
understands women

198
00:10:28,672 --> 00:10:29,631
Hold on!

199
00:10:29,631 --> 00:10:31,299
What do you want?

200
00:10:31,299 --> 00:10:32,759
Don't look at me like you think

201
00:10:32,759 --> 00:10:34,886
I'm going to be a complete
waste of your time.

202
00:10:34,886 --> 00:10:37,973
I'll have you know that I'm not
only a master of martial arts,

203
00:10:37,973 --> 00:10:40,726
but I'm also an expert
in the art of love.

204
00:10:40,726 --> 00:10:44,855
Wait! Just wait! Listen to me!
Seriously, women love me!

205
00:10:44,855 --> 00:10:47,607
Now I might not look it,
but when I was a younger fella,

206
00:10:47,607 --> 00:10:49,067
the ladies found me
completely irresistible

207
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:50,902
and considered to
be quite the hunk!

208
00:10:50,902 --> 00:10:52,988
Back in the old days
people used to call me

209
00:10:52,988 --> 00:10:54,364
the Don Juan of China!

210
00:10:54,364 --> 00:10:55,490
Right...

211
00:10:55,490 --> 00:10:58,452
Hey, wait just a second!
You scoff now,

212
00:10:58,452 --> 00:11:00,078
but you'll be singing
a different tune

213
00:11:00,078 --> 00:11:02,539
when you see this picture
of me from way back!

214
00:11:02,539 --> 00:11:05,083
Y-You were a "pretty boy"?!

215
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,711
The years have been pretty
tough on you, haven't they?

216
00:11:07,711 --> 00:11:11,923
I don't need your
pity young one.

217
00:11:11,923 --> 00:11:14,259
But enough of that, if you
really want to take her

218
00:11:14,259 --> 00:11:17,387
on a date you should just be
a man about it and ask her out.

219
00:11:17,387 --> 00:11:19,723
That's easy for you to say,
you're not doing the asking.

220
00:11:19,723 --> 00:11:22,225
If it was a normal girl the
worst thing that could happen

221
00:11:22,225 --> 00:11:24,144
is she might turn me
down, but with Miu,

222
00:11:24,144 --> 00:11:26,897
I've got be extra careful
so she doesn't take me down!

223
00:11:26,897 --> 00:11:28,148
Relationships are tough,

224
00:11:28,148 --> 00:11:31,026
and it sounds like you
don't trust the girl--

225
00:11:31,026 --> 00:11:33,862
then how can there be love?

226
00:11:33,862 --> 00:11:36,156
No, it's not that I don't
trust her, the real problem

227
00:11:36,156 --> 00:11:38,575
is that I don't know her
as well as I'd like!

228
00:11:38,575 --> 00:11:40,118
This special
edition's on sale.

229
00:11:40,118 --> 00:11:41,578
Since you and I know each other,

230
00:11:41,578 --> 00:11:44,206
I can give you a pretty good
deal. I take only cash.

231
00:11:44,206 --> 00:11:46,541
Wait, you've been taking
secret photos of Miu?!

232
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:47,959
You made 'em into a book?!

233
00:11:47,959 --> 00:11:49,377
How could you?!

234
00:11:49,377 --> 00:11:51,379
What? You're upset?

235
00:11:51,379 --> 00:11:53,465
I swear, people like you...

236
00:11:53,465 --> 00:11:54,633
...make me so happy!

237
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:57,135
Thank you so much for doing
this, you really have no idea

238
00:11:57,135 --> 00:11:59,221
what this means to me!
I owe you big time!

239
00:11:59,221 --> 00:12:01,306
Please, don't mention it,
that's what sensei's are for!

240
00:12:01,306 --> 00:12:03,600
If you're interested, I've got
one of Shigure on sale too?

241
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:06,478
Akisame did say that the key
to a successful relationship

242
00:12:06,478 --> 00:12:09,564
is understanding as much as you
possibly can about your partner!

243
00:12:09,564 --> 00:12:12,526
Hey! What are you
guys doing out here?

244
00:12:12,526 --> 00:12:15,445
N-nothing! We started
talking about life!

245
00:12:15,445 --> 00:12:16,947
What is it? What do you want?!

246
00:12:16,947 --> 00:12:18,615
I don't know what your
plans are tomorrow.

247
00:12:18,615 --> 00:12:21,159
I need to run to the grocery
store to pick up some stuff,

248
00:12:21,159 --> 00:12:23,995
